title: Transatlantic liners, 1945-1980 (gnv64)
description:
Transatlantic liners, 1945-1980
by William H Mille
Arco Publishing | 1981 | ISBN-10: 0668052678 | 222 pages | scanned PDF | 52.1 mb

The ocean liner, like the steam locomotive, is a source of fascination as a lost art form, a dinosaur of travel, a symbol of a more leisurely and luxurious life style in an age before air travel came into its own. With one or two exceptions, the ships which served the the graet transatlantic trade during rhc glorious heyday of the port-to-port passenger ship are gone. It is a fitting tribute to the splendor of the era that they should be recorded in a complete catalog, which gives each ship, large or small, it s plaice in the star-studded cast.

The statistical data and hi story for (3eh vessel arc given, accompanied by a photograph and listed under the company which owned her from An mean Banner Lines to Zim Lines, Transatlantic Liners 1945-1980 provides a unique record and a magnificent window on a golden era of the past
